Two separate issues here:

### 1. `StaticResource` doesn't update at runtime
`StaticResource` resolves **once** at load time. Switch to **`DynamicResource`** so bindings re-evaluate when the dictionary changes:

```xml
<!-- ✗ won't update -->
<Label TextColor="{StaticResource PrimaryTextColor}" />

<!-- ✓ updates on theme swap -->
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
```

Then swap themes by clearing and merging dictionaries:

```csharp
var mergedDictionaries = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
mergedDictionaries.Clear();
mergedDictionaries.Add(useDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
```

### 2. Activity restart on system dark mode change
Android destroys and recreates the `Activity` when `uiMode` changes. Tell Android your app handles it itself in `MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
[Activity(
    Theme = "@style/Maui.SplashTheme",
    ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.UiMode
        | ConfigChanges.ScreenSize
        | ConfigChanges.Orientation)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

Then detect the system change and apply your theme:

```csharp
public override void OnConfigurationChanged(Configuration newConfig)
{
    base.OnConfigurationChanged(newConfig);

    bool isDark = (newConfig.UiMode & UiMode.NightMask) == UiMode.NightYes;

    var merged = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
    merged.Clear();
    merged.Add(isDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
}
```

**TL;DR** — `StaticResource` → `DynamicResource` fixes runtime switching; adding `ConfigChanges.UiMode` stops the restart.
